<dl id="n40043b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40043b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40043b"> 43(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Asmodeus / Mammon</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The development of the conception continued in later Judaism, which was probably more strongly influenced by Persian dualism. It is doubtful, however, whether the Asmodeus (q.v.) of the book of Tobit is the same as the Aeshma Daewa of the Bundahesh. He is the evil spirit who slew the seven husbands of Sara (iii. 8), and the name probably means &ldquo;Destroyer.&rdquo; <small> &ldquo;DEVIL&rdquo; <a name="EBDV" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDV"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) VIII 122</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
